               <p>I lodge at <placeName id="t17801206-48-crimeloc246">No. 10, Brick-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17801206-48-crimeloc246" type="placeName" value="No. 10, Brick-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17801206-48-crimeloc246" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17801206-48-off244 t17801206-48-crimeloc246"></join>. On Wednesday last I went out of my apartment about four o'clock in the afternoon. I returned again in a quarter of an hour. I found my room door open. I locked it when I went out. I went into my room; I saw the prisoner almost by the fire-place. I asked her what she did there? She said, she was come to enquire for a Mrs. Williams, that she had a letter from her husband, who was on board a ship. I told her that was an idle excuse. She had something in her apron. I called down my shop-mate, 
               <persName id="t17801206-48-person493">
                  Thomas
                   Edwards
               <interp inst="t17801206-48-person493" type="surname" value="Edwards"></interp>
